(8, '2011-01-25 13:36:06', 1, 'SensorAPI', '<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\r\n<p>Welcome to the SensorAPI that provides interface to our sensor testbed. It is designed as a REST web service. Due to read-only nature of the data only GET methods are implemented and accessible for the user.</p>\r\n<p>At the moment only XML is used as internet media type.</p>\r\n<h2>Getting started</h2>\r\n<p>Requests to the web service can be triggered from mash-up javascript applications, PHP framework or any other software.</p>\r\n<p>Here is an example of JavaScript/jQuery code that handles one of our requests:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<pre>function loadedKeywords(data) {<br />&nbsp; var HTML = "";<br />&nbsp; $(data).find("keyword").each(function() {<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;var keyword = $(this);<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;var keywordName = keyword.attr("name");&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;var weight = keyword.attr("weight");<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;size = Math.round(weight * 50) + 8;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;HTML += "&lt;font style=\\"font-size: " + size + "px\\"&gt;&lt;a href=\\"javascript:filterByKeyword(''" + keywordName + "'');\\"&gt;" + keywordName + "&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt; ";&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />&nbsp; });<br />&nbsp; $("#div-keywords").html(HTML);<br />}</pre>\r\n<pre>$(function() {</pre>\r\n<pre>&nbsp; // keyword cloud<br />&nbsp; $.ajax({<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; url: ''http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/get-keywords'',<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; success: loadedKeywords<br />&nbsp; });</pre>\r\n<pre>});<br /><br /></pre>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>If you decide to use our API, you are kindly invited to <a href="mailto:klemen.kenda@ijs.si?subject=Sensor+API">let us know</a> about it.</p>\r\n<h2>Error reporting</h2>\r\n<p>In case an error occurs while processing a request an XML is returned, that contains description of the error.</p>\r\n<p>XML looks like this:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<pre>&lt;errors&gt;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;error&gt;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Description of the error.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/error&gt;<br />&lt;/errors&gt;&nbsp;</pre>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h2>Reference</h2>\r\n<p>XML response description in this reference contains XML tree explaination. In the tree the <strong>bold </strong>nodes represent an XML element and normal (non-bold) nodes represent element attributes.</p>\r\n<h3>Data Types</h3>\r\n<p><strong>int</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>integer</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>float</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>real number</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>string</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>string</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>date</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>MySQL-like date string formatted as YYYY-MM-DD</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>time</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>MySQL-like datetime string formatted as YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p><strong>duration_type</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>integer, representing duration period:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>0 - reserved</li>\r\n<li>1 - 1 minute</li>\r\n<li>2 - 5 minutes</li>\r\n<li>3 - 15 minutes</li>\r\n<li>4 - 1 hour</li>\r\n<li>5 - 6 hours</li>\r\n<li>6 - 1 day</li>\r\n<li>7 - 1 week</li>\r\n<li>8 - 1 month</li>\r\n<li>9 - 1 year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>sensors-on-node</h3>\r\n<p>Returns list of sensor_ids (sensors), installed on the node.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters: </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>1: </strong>int <em>node_id</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Result: </strong>XML&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>HTTP request:&nbsp;</strong></strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/sensors-on-node/par1</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> <strong>node</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>sensor type id&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n<li>n (int) - <em>number of sensors<br /></em></li>\r\n<li><em></em><strong>sensor</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>sensor id</em></li>\r\n<li>type (int) - <em>sensor type id</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>node-from-sensor</h3>\r\n<p>Returns node_id from provided sensor_id.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters: </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>1: </strong>int&nbsp;<em>sensor_type_id</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Result: </strong>XML&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>HTTP request:&nbsp;</strong></strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/node-from-sensor/par1</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> <strong>node</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>node id&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n<li>sensorid (int) - <em>sensor id</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>sensor-type</h3>\r\n<p>Returns sensor type (including feature of measurement and unit of measurement to the user). Same info is also included in current-state.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters: </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>1: </strong>int&nbsp;<em>sensor_type_id</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Result: </strong>XML&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>HTTP request:&nbsp;</strong></strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/sensor-type/par1</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> <strong>sensortype</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>sensor type id&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n<li>type (string) - <em>type of the sensor</em></li>\r\n<li><em></em>featureofmeasurement (string) - <em>feature of measurement</em></li>\r\n<li><em></em>unitofmeasurement (string) - <em>unit of measurement</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>current-state</h3>\r\n<p>Returns data about all nodes, sensors installed on them and the most recent timestamped measurements.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters: </strong>none<br /><strong>Result: </strong>XML&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>HTTP request:&nbsp;</strong></strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/current-state</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>current-state</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>nodes</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>records (int) - <em>number of nodes</em></li>\r\n<li><strong>node</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>internal id of the node</em></li>\r\n<li>name (string) - <em>identifier of the node</em></li>\r\n<li>latitude (double) - <em>latitude of the node</em></li>\r\n<li>longitude (double) - longitude of the node</li>\r\n<li><strong>sensor</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>internal id of the sensor</em></li>\r\n<li>sensortypeid (int) - <em>internal id of the type of the sensor</em></li>\r\n<li>featureofmeasurement (string) - <em>human readable feature of measurement</em></li>\r\n<li>unitofmeasurement (string) - <em>human readable unit of measurement</em></li>\r\n<li>lastmeasurement (double) - <em>value of the last measurement from the sensor</em></li>\r\n<li>measurementtime (time) -<em>&nbsp;MySQL fromatted timestamp of the measurement</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>get-measurements</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>1: </strong>int&nbsp;<em>sensor_id</em></li>\r\n<li><strong>2: </strong>date&nbsp;<em>start_date</em></li>\r\n<li><strong>3: </strong>duration_type&nbsp;<em>time_dt</em></li>\r\n<li><strong>4: </strong>duration_type&nbsp;<em>aggregation_dt</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Result: </strong>XML</p>\r\n<p><strong>HTTP request: </strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/get-measurements/par1:par2:par3:par4</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>get-measurements</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>sensor</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - sensor id from the base</li>\r\n<li>typeid (int) - sensor type id</li>\r\n<li>unitofmeasurement (string) - human-readable unit of measurement</li>\r\n<li>featureofmeasurement (string) - human-readable feature of measurement</li>\r\n<li><strong>interval</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>avg (double) - average value on the aggregation interval</li>\r\n<li>min (double) - minimal value on the aggregation intrerval</li>\r\n<li>max (double) - maximum value on the aggregation interval</li>\r\n<li>n (int) - number of measurements in the aggregation interval</li>\r\n<li>sum (double) - sum of all measurements in the aggregation interval</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>get-keywords</h3>\r\n<p>Returns keywords (feature of measurement) and their weight (according to their frequency).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters: </strong>none<br /><strong>Result: </strong>XML&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>HTTP request:&nbsp;</strong></strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/get-keywords</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> <strong>keywords</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>keyword</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>name (string) - <em>feature of measurement</em></li>\r\n<li>weight (float) - <em>relative weight according to the frequency of the sensor, measuring this feature, in the testbed</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h3>get-clusters</h3>\r\n<p>Returns clusters of nodes, enriched with Wikipedia and Geonames data.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Parameters: </strong>none<br /><strong>Result: </strong>XML&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>HTTP request:&nbsp;</strong></strong>http://sensors.ijs.si/xml/get-clusters</p>\r\n<p><strong>XML response description:</strong></p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> <strong>clusters</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>cluster</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>nodes (int) - <em>number of nodes in the cluster</em></li>\r\n<li>latitude (float) - <em>mean latitude of the cluster</em></li>\r\n<li>longitude (float) - <em>mean longitude of the cluster</em></li>\r\n<li>place (string) - <em>place name from Geonames</em></li>\r\n<li><strong>node</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>id (int) - <em>id of the node in the system</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>wiki</strong> - <em>nearest Wikipedia entry; </em>content (string) - <em>description of the entry from Wikipedia<br /></em> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>title (string) <em>- title from Wikipedia</em></li>\r\n<li>url (string) - <em>url to Wikipedia entry</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>hierarchy</strong> - <em>toponym hierarchy from Geonames</em><br /> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>toponym</strong> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>name (string) - <em>toponym name from Geonames</em></li>\r\n<li>fcode (string) - <em>Geonames-specific classificator of the toponym</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<h2>Examples</h2>\r\n<p>Check:&nbsp;<a href="/sl/index.html" target="_blank">http://sensors.ijs.si</a></p>', '', '', 50, 'api/index', '', '', ''),
