(11, '2011-05-16 20:07:21', 1, 'Electricity saving', '<h2>Electricity saving in Miren</h2>\r\n<p>Nodes on the light-poles in Miren are programmed the way they start dimming the lights at 23:00 and then restore the luminosity at 5:00 in the morning. Transition of the luminosity is linear and it lasts 15 minutes. Lights are dimmed by 25% during the night.</p>\r\n<p>Dimming (in this article this needs to be understood as ratio of control voltage controlling lights luminosity) is shown in the chart below.</p>\r\n<p><img src="/slike/upload/dimmingvstime.jpg" alt="" width="736" height="494" /></p>\r\n<p>Red line represents <em>no dimming</em>, used by nodes in Kostanjevica.</p>\r\n<h3>Characteristics: Power vs. dimming</h3>\r\n<p>Power characteristics has been measured for the lights in Miren and is shown in the chart below.</p>\r\n<p><img src="/slike/upload/characteristics.jpg" alt="" width="742" height="426" /></p>\r\n<p>Higher end of the characteristics has been fitted by an analytic function:</p>\r\n<p><img src="/slike/upload/characteristicshigh.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="404" /></p>\r\n<h3>Power consumption</h3>\r\n<p>We have measured power consumption of the light with the full luminosity.</p>\r\n<p>P[full] = 37.2W</p>\r\n<p>With the fitted function we have calculated power consumtion at the 75% luminosity control voltage:</p>\r\n<p>P[75%] = 31.8W</p>\r\n<p>Note that luminosity voltage drop by 25% is followed by power drop of only ~14%.</p>\r\n<p>Power consumption during the night is shown below.</p>\r\n<p><img src="/slike/upload/powervstime.jpg" alt="" width="722" height="493" /></p>\r\n<p>Red line represents <em>no dimming</em>, used by nodes in Kostanjevica.</p>\r\n<h3>Energy saved</h3>\r\n<p>Integrating power over time (during the night) gives us electrical energy, consumed by the light. We have calculated energy usage for both cases: no dimming and dimming the lights during the night.</p>\r\n<p>W(full) = 0.372kWh<br />W(dimming) = 0.341kWh</p>\r\n<p>Energy saved ~8.3%, which gives us approximately 1kWh per light per month.</p>\r\n<h3>Technical details</h3>\r\n<p>Measurements have been done with Grah Automotive LSL 30 lights. We made an assumption that lights are switched on at 20:15 (with full luminosity) and switched off at 6:15.</p>', '', '', 50, 'electricity-saving', '', '', ''),
